Land Rig Driller
05 May 2014 04:39 PM - UAE
..The Driller is responsible for the deployment and guidance of the rig crew and the use of the rig equipment, in accordance with KCAD Policies so as to safely and efficiently conduct the Operator's drilling program. ROLE â¢ Demonstrate and promote safety leadership to ensure that the crew works in the safest manner. â¢ Lead and direct the crew in fulfilling their designated duties. â¢ Plan and conduct Rig-floor and related activities so as to meet the highest applicable standard of international oilfield practice. â¢ Monitor and adjust the drilling parameters and take those necessary actions so as to optimize the drilling process and safeguard the integrity of the well. â¢ Work constructively with the Operator's representative and with third party service companies so as to contribute to collaborative working relationships at the rig site. â¢ Take immediate remedial action in the event of an incipient or actual emergency or incident. â¢ To advise the Tool Pusher and Operator's representative of any issues as appropriate. RESPONSIBILITIES ï Safety â¢ Personally responsible for own safety and conducting safety to the standards of KCAD Policies and Procedures. â¢ Promote and promulgate KCAD safety program. â¢ Apply KCAD safety policies and practice in rig operations, act as a role model to crew members in all safety matters. â¢ Conduct and record TBT for the crew, achieve the participation and contribution of crew members. â¢ Play a full part in rig safety meetings. â¢ Conduct safety inspections of rig equipment and hold training drills as directed by Tool Pusher. â¢ Contribute to New Employee Safety Inductions. â¢ Ensure that all activities, including those of third party contractors, are conducted using safe working practices and using the designated Personal Protection Equipment (PPE) ï Operations â¢ Plan the tourly operations and conduct pre-job piefings or J.S.A.'s for the crew on activities. â¢ Operate the rig equipment within its designed p